name: World's Smallest Simon
description: World’s Smallest Simon is an EXACT replica of the original electronic memory game! Only 2 inches in diameter, featuring four color window buttons and authentic tonal sounds. Follow the light and sound patterns up to 73 sequences that increase in speed as you advance. As the game progresses, the sequences become progressively longer and more complex, testing players’ memory and concentration. Simon’s timeless appeal lies in its simplicity and addictive nature, making it a beloved choice for both casual gamers and enthusiasts alike. For ages 6 and up.

name: National Geographic Glow-in-the-Dark Gecko Dissection Lab

This exciting science kit has everything kids need to safely explore gecko anatomy, with easy-to-use tools and a detailed learning guide that makes identifying each organ and bone a whole lot of fun! There are five different bone sections to explore and seven major organs. Plus, the bones glow in the dark! Once kids have completed their first dissection, they can reassemble the bones and organs and then use the included refill pack and mold for a second dissection. This lab offers an unforgettable, hands-on science experience kids will absolutely love! Get the Glow-in-the-Dark Gecko Dissection Lab today!

name: CreArt Think Pink - 5x7
description: Picture your favorite child’s delight when they finish their very own flamingo painting and “Think Pink” with our CreArt Painting by Numbers set! Watch your young one’s imagination take flight as they create a fun painting featuring a “Think Pink” feathered flamingo! They can relax with this fun and satisfying paint-by-number kit, complete with everything needed to make and display their very own masterpiece. Painting is a snap, with color-outlined sections and matching, odorless acrylic paints to ensure picture-perfect results. Finish in about 4 hours, let dry, then use the included frame to proudly display your budding artist’s talent! Looking for a fun activity that keeps your kids off their screens? Help them discover their inner artist with CreArt, our high-quality Painting by Numbers sets! With kid-friendly images designed to match abilities, budding artists can enjoy completing their very own painting in just a few hours. Easy-to-see colored outlines distinguish each section, helping kids achieve great results. Painting is a fun, creative activity that can also improve dexterity and concentration while providing a sense of satisfaction! CreArt contains everything children need to create their painting: a high-quality, thick painting board; 10 water-based, opaque acrylic paints in numbered pots; pallet to hold the easy-open/resealable paint pots steady; durable, fine-point paintbrush; easy-to-follow guide sheet; and frame to display their finished artwork. Makes a great gift!

name: Snap Circuits Flight Deck
description: How does a plane fly? How does electricity work? How do you create and launch paper airplanes? How does air pressure impact aerodynamics? Six projects provide hours of play, helps kids understand STEM and how the world works. FLIGHT DECK® was designed to allow kids to discover the science of electricity, physics and provide hours of play. The simple design and flexible application of parts allows for 6 unique projects. Kids will build a paper airplanes and send them flying. They will install a motor circuit and launch flying saucers. Build a circuit that launches ping pong balls Additional projects include creating artistic patterns on a spinning wheel and learning about air pressure by levitating balls over a fan. FLIGHT DECK® includes easy to follow directions that allow kids to work independently, build confidence, and learn how the world works. It's the ultimate STEM toy!

name: Pizza Rat Macaroon - 6.5 inch
description: This plush Pizza Rat Macaroon is the undisputed ruler of the city’s underground train system! Sitting up proudly, this diminutive rodent musters all the dignity he is able and looks out over his kingdom with small, dark eyes. Pastel pink accents complement our Rat’s pale gray coat of soft plush fur. He wears a cape bearing the shape and appearance of a slice of pizza, a symbol of good fortune and plenty amongst the city’s rats. And if all that wasn’t enough to convince you of his royal status, our little Rat King wears a tiny, golden crown atop his head. What they say is true, if you can make it in New York City, you can make it anywhere, and this whimsical Pizza Rat stuffed animal has come out at the top of the heap!

name: Countaloupe
description: Use your melon to ripen your chances. Use your melon to ripen your chances in Countaloupe: a slice and dice game of risk and reward! Roll the dice, count your seeds, and be the first player to get rid of all the slices in your deck. Stop there or keep rolling, but be careful—one rotten roll of the dice can ripen or squash your chance for sweet victory in Countaloupe! Perfect for STEM learners! What’s Inside? 4 x 16 Cards 5 regular Dice 1 'Chance' Die 1 'Nope' Chip Rules Ages: 7+ Players: 2-4 Play Time: 15mins

name: Word Treasures A Pirate's Adventure
description: Welcome, Matey! Set sail for six different pirated themed games, including three levels of scavenger hunts, a memory game, matching game and three puzzle options. name: Pairs in Pears 2.0
description: The playfully patterned word pairing match-up! PAIRS in PEARS is a playfully patterned word game that grows with your family! This competitive "race to build-a-grid" game offers varied levels of play—including engaging and fun, pre school activities—which then progress to a challenging, addictive game for all ages! With four full alphabet sets in four distinct designs, and multiple game variations, PAIRS in PEARS truly has something for everyone! What’s Inside? 124 Letter Tiles Rules Ages: 3+ Players: 1-4 Play Time: 30 mins or less

name: Pizzasaurus Shaped Box Game
description: For dinosaur and pizza-loving kids–Pizzasaurus is the slap-tastic topping matching game. This original game for 2-4 players, ages 4+, includes 33 cards, a wooden die, and 3 shaped pizzasaurus tiles. To play, players roll the die and try to match the pizza toppings to collect cards. If a player flips a card that matches a pizzasaurus tile, all players race to be the first to slap the matching tile.

name: John Deere Busy Driver
description: Now your little farmer can experience “driving” their very own tractor with the John Deere Busy Driver loaded with a dozen interactive and fun activities. Get busy with the harvest by turning the tethered key to start the tractor’s engine, then shift gears by pulling down or pushing up the left lever. Back up with a beep, beep noise when you pull towards the turtle or prepare for a fast action motion sound when you push towards the rabbit. Switch the orange lever to flash the turn signal arrows and make some noise with the working horn on the spinning steering wheel. Push the music button to keep a long work day a little more exciting with a lively tune or spin the odometer to make it click, click, click. If you run into trouble, press the hazard button to make the turn signals flash with a warning beep, beep sound. Ages 12 months +

description: Say hello to Alexander Girlz! These fashionable girls spread joy wherever they go, and help kids be kind and dream big! These beautiful 14-Inch poseable dolls have rooted hair, fixed eyes, and are dressed in stylish outfits. Zola is dressed in a full-length tulle skirt with a cropped tie front tee layered under a denim jacket. Alexander Girlz have lots of fun sharing friendship! These beautiful 14-Inch poseable fashion dolls with rooted hair and fixed eyes are dressed in stylish outfits and wear warm smiles. They spread joy wherever they go, and help kids be kind, dream big, and play imaginatively! Engage your child in imaginative play with this doll, teaching kindness and empathy. Doll wipes clean with damp cloth. Features dark skin, brown eyes, and black hair. Recommended for ages 3 and up.
